Ahmed Areff, News24(File) (Ian Carbutt, The Witness) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - An East Rand man shot dead two men allegedly trying to rob him in his Norkem Park home, police said on Friday.The home owner and a friend were relaxing outside the house when two armed men confronted them around 21:00 on Thursday, Lieutenant Colonel Lungelo Dlamini said.&nbsp;The men forced the owner and his friend into the home at gunpoint.&nbsp; "Whilst inside the house, the owner managed to take his firearm and a shoot-out ensued between him and the suspects. Two suspects were fatally shot and were found in possession of two unlicensed firearms," Dlamini said.&nbsp;A silver Suzuki, believed to be their getaway car, was found a few metres from the house. The two suspects had not yet been identified, but it was suspected they had been involved in other serious and violent crimes.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.